Path: godot/classes/class_window.rst
Summary: This chunk describes the signals emitted by a Window node, covering events like visibility changes, focus, user input, file drops, and display property updates.

Signal: about_to_popup()
Emitted right after the popup() method is called, before the Window appears or does anything.

Signal: close_requested()
Emitted when the Window's close button is pressed or when popup_window is enabled and the user clicks outside the window. This signal can be used to handle window closing, for example, by connecting it to the hide() method.

Signal: dpi_changed()
Emitted when the Window's DPI changes as a result of OS-level changes, such as moving the window from a Retina display to a lower-resolution one. Note: This is only implemented on macOS and Linux (Wayland).

Signal: files_dropped(files: PackedStringArray)
Emitted when files are dragged from the OS file manager and dropped in the game window. The `files` argument is a list of file paths.
GDScript:
    func _ready():
        get_window().files_dropped.connect(on_files_dropped)

    func on_files_dropped(files):
        print(files)

Note: This signal only works with native windows, i.e., the main window and Window-derived nodes when Viewport.gui_embed_subwindows is disabled in the main viewport.

Signal: focus_entered()
Emitted when the Window gains focus.

Signal: focus_exited()
Emitted when the Window loses its focus.

Signal: go_back_requested()
Emitted when a go back request is sent (e.g., pressing the "Back" button on Android), right after Node.NOTIFICATION_WM_GO_BACK_REQUEST.

Signal: mouse_entered()
Emitted when the mouse cursor enters the Window's visible area that is not occluded by other Controls or windows, provided its Viewport.gui_disable_input is `false` and regardless of whether it's currently focused.

Signal: mouse_exited()
Emitted when the mouse cursor leaves the Window's visible area that is not occluded by other Controls or windows, provided its Viewport.gui_disable_input is `false` and regardless of whether it's currently focused.

Signal: nonclient_window_input(event: InputEvent)
Emitted when a mouse event is received by the custom decoration area defined by `nonclient_area`, and normal input to the window is blocked (such as when it has an exclusive child opened). The `event`'s position is in the embedder's coordinate system.

Signal: output_max_linear_value_changed(output_max_linear_value: float)
Emitted when the value returned by get_output_max_linear_value() changes. This occurs when HDR output is enabled or disabled, or when any HDR output luminance values of the window change (e.g., the player adjusts screen brightness or moves the window to a different screen). `output_max_linear_value` is the new value.

Signal: theme_changed()
Emitted when the NOTIFICATION_THEME_CHANGED notification is sent.

Signal: title_changed()
Emitted when the window title bar text is changed.

Signal: titlebar_changed()
Emitted when window title bar decorations are changed, for example, when a macOS window enters or exits full-screen mode, or the extend-to-title flag is changed.

Signal: visibility_changed()
Emitted when the Window is made visible or disappears.

Signal: window_input(event: InputEvent)
Emitted when the Window is currently focused and receives any input. The received event is passed as an argument. The event's position, if present, is in the embedder's coordinate system.
---CHUNK---
